definition.value: Any deviation from the normal range of concentration of a metabolite in the cerebrospinal fluid.
Any deviation from the normal range of a protein concentration in the cerebrospinal fluid.
An increase above normal limits of the ratio of the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) albumin concentration to serum albumin concentration.

label.value: High myoinositol in brain by MRS

definition.value: Any anomaly of cell structure.
An abnormality of the processes that maintain the redox environment of a cell or compartment within a cell, that is, the balance between reduction and oxidation chemical reactions.
A deviation from the normal concentration of beta globulin. The beta globulins are a group of globular (globe-shaped) proteins in blood.
Increased level of beta 2-microglobulins in the urine.
A type of hair loss characterized by an abnormal increase in dormant, telogen stage hair follicles.
A history of repeated fungal infections located on the sole of the foot, usually manifested by scaling, maceration, and itching.

A papule (circumscribed, solid elevation of skin with no visible fluid, varying in size from a pinhead to less than 10mm in diameter at the widest point) that exhibits increased pigmentation (is darker) compared to the surrounding skin.
A plaque (a solid, raised, plateau-like (flat-topped) lesion greater than 1 cm in diameter) with a red or reddish color often associated with inflammation or irritation.

A macule (flat, distinct, discolored area of skin less than 1 cm wide that does not involve any change in the thickness or texture of the skin) with a red or reddish color often associated with inflammation or irritation.

Multiple foci of adipocytes within the testicular interstitium, usually presenting as multiple bilateral ill-defined hyperechoic intratesticular lesions of different sizes but generally with maximum diameter of 4 mm.
Calcified deposits in soft tissue structures outside a joint.
A pathological neglect of personal needs and well-being that includes attending to self-grooming, personal care and the attention to cleanliness of personal space.

A type of spinal dysraphism presenting as a subcutaneous fatty mass, that is, a spinal defect associated with lipomatous tissue, and covered by skin. The most usual location for lipomyelomeningocele is at the gluteal cleft.
Absence of one half of the vertebral body in the cervical spine.
A deviation from the normal concentration of thyroglobulin, a protein produced in the thyroid gland that acts as a precursor to thyrroid hormones.
An abnormal elevation of the concentration of thyroglobulin, a protein produced in the thyroid gland that acts as a precursor to thyrroid hormones.
The outer labia are sealed together.
Any structural anomaly of the bladder.
Narrowing of a vein due to intimal hyperplasia and fibrosis.
Redness of the skin of the palm of the hand and the sole of the foot caused by hyperemia of the capillaries in the lower layers of the skin.
Any anomaly of the function of a coronary artery.
Absence of ceruloplasmin in the blood.
Obesity with a body mass index of 30 to 34.9 kg per square meter.
Obesity with a body mass index of 35 to 39.9 kg per square meter.
Obesity with a body mass index of 40 kg per square meter or higher.
Increased body weight with a body mass index of 25-29.9 kg per square meter.

label.value: Anomalous coronary artery arising from the opposite sinus
